line_1: I envied Heaven the time she pray'd;
Who often, but without success, have pray'd
The hoary Priest oft while he suppliant pray'd,
line_2: On his own Altar was a Victim made.

line_1: In vain I wept, and 'twas in vain I pray'd,
line_2: For all my Pray'rs were to a Tyger made;

line_1: The fretful youth to Cupid prayed;
line_2: The ardent suppliant's will to aid.

line_1: So fixt her thoughts, that even in Dreams she Pray'd,
line_2: So Constantly her Pious Vows she pay'd,

line_1: As at thy shrine I fondly pray'd;
line_2: All these an offering oft I've paid,

To Thee, O LORD of Life, I pray'd,

line_2: And with strong sympathy the youth survey'd:

line_1: And set the bearded Leek, to which I pray'd:
line_2: To Shrubs and Plants my vile Devotion paid;

line_1: And most devoutly begg'd and pray'd
line_2: Not to be wash'd by careless maid,

line_1: And fond paternal care his counsel pray'd;
line_2: His guidance to vouchsafe and friendly aid;
